charge earlier this year he would not seek election to a fourth 
term as mayor his decision touched off a chain reaction that 
guarantees the city a toptobottom realignment of political 
leaders next year 
dixon won with 35 percent of the vote to 25 percent for city 
councilman john ray her closest rival in complete totals from the 
citys 140 precincts delegate walter fauntroy who gave up his 
nonvoting house seat to seek barrys job finished last in the 
fiveway field 
in the race for a nonvoting senate seat jackson had 56 percent 
of those ballots in a fiveway race for a pair of nominations 
